caption: Waiter Was Garbino.....Always Acted Like She Was In A Hurry(No Time To Cater To)....I Had To Tell Her To Slow Down When She Walked Us To Our Table....Food Took Waaaaaay Tooo Looooong To Arrive. She Ask Did We Want Bread And We Said Yes But She Brought It Out Way After The Appetizer Arrived Without Plates...Also We Ordered A Side Of Lobster Rice That Was NEVER Brought Out...We Waited To SEE If She Would Notice OR If It was On The Bill....AND IT WASN'T!@#$%^&* But The FOOD Was GooD!

Celebrated husband's 50th birthday. Service was excellent and food was fantastic. They prepared a special menu saying Happy 50th birthday, all staff upon checkin to passing our table wished him a happy birthday, and they also gave him a free dessert. Wasn't our first visit there and definitely won't be our last.
Excellent food and better service. It is a above average and you should expect to pay for it. Great experience and good people.
Excellent food!!!
Amazing food and service. Worth every penny.

On a Tuesday evening I decided to visit the restaurant looking for fresh seafood. I visited  solo and sat at the bar.  When I arrived there were only two other patrons at the bar. I was greeted and I ordered a drink and the bartend disappeared for what seemed like 10 minutes, when see returned to the bar area she not acknowledge me for another ten minutes, five of which, I was hoping to order another drink and an appetizer. I thought then, I should close my tab and find another place to eat. I decided to be patient and see if things would get better...they did not. The other two patrons at the bar left, so it was only me. The service did not improve. I was committed to making every effort to be fair...silly me.  Being the only one seated at the bar,  I felt like i was on a deserted island. The restaurant was not busy but the service was absolutely terrible. I order my meal,  king crab legs and they did not taste fresh at all and were over cooked. Long story short, after dropping over $200 for a meal for my self the experience was extremely disappointing. I would not recommend visiting this restaurant under it's current management. So many other places to eat that can offer better dining experience at a lower price point.  Disappointed diner

They accept reservations for parties of 4 (not sure of party-size limit).  The food was incredible!  The crab cakes were delicious and the sides are very generous.  I highly recommend the lobster and crab mac'n'cheese.  The key lime pie was also delicious and pretty big.  It is a little dim inside, which made it somewhat difficult to read the menu, but that is the only downside to this restaurant, if you want to even call it a downside.
I took my Mom there and we had an incredible meal. Our server Amanda did an outstanding job!!!

The experience last night with my fiancé was absolutely one of the best experiences we have ever had dining out. Amanda was our server and she was hands down the best server we have ever had. She was knowledgeable, friendly, personable, and professional. She recommended the swordfish and dynamite it, let me tell you, I love seafood and this was absolutely amazing. Ben Carroll, Amanda, and the rest of Oceanaire team gave us a night out we will not forget. We look forward to the next time. Thank you all. - Jess and Whitney

The swordfish was superb and perfectly cooked and the key lime pie is a truly excellent way to end the evening. The servers were attentive and very knowledgeable of the menu. The oysters were fresh and a bargain at $1 apiece (happy hour price). The meal was pricey but not overpriced.
expensive but good seafood.

The servers were wonderful but there were quite a few issues with my experience. One of six oysters was bad and I discovered that after putting it into my mouth. And the caviar for a mere $150 took like 25 minutes to get. Unacceptable.  While the manager came over and apologize he did nothing to rectify the situation. Unfortunately the manager is ill seasoned to provide exceptional service at this location. He's argumentative and seems to have the position that the customers might be trying to get something for free. I guess spending almost $500 for dinner and wine with a whopping party of one is isn't an indication to him that I might know what fine dining is and I might have the money for it and I expect to be treated with decency.   This guy needs to retrained or he needs to be retrained. I've dined at multiple locations across the United States and this gentleman is the worst manager I've ever encountered. To boot until I argued a bit after receiving the sour oyster this guy only took one of the six oysters off the check. I had to try to give him a little schooling on fine dining and customer service and ask him to take all six off the check. He finally did so.
First time to this restaurant.  The food was phenomenal.  The wait staff was courteous and knowledgeable! Wonderful experience!
The service was great and the food was delicious.

The food was very good and there were no problems with curbside pickup-- other than the employee calling me "Babe" (I'm old enough to be his mother, smh). However, I totally agree with other online reviews: VERY overpriced for the portion sizes, entrees and appetizers both. Glad we each ordered a soup or salad or we would have still been hungry.
Best sea food ever
Best oysters in Indianapolis.
Excellent service, nice atmosphere and great food. A wonderful place to celebrate a special occasion.
OMG LOVED IT!!!

My wife and I had an amazing Valentine's day at Oceanaire. This was our first time here and  to say the service here was exceptional is an understatement.  Jesse and Aaron did a fabulous job.  Jesse recommended the chicken fried lobster.  My wife could not have been more satisfied with this dish. It was the perfect mix of sweet and spicy. The King crab was by far the best I've ever had. I wasn't sure how much to order. We decided on a pound and a half and it was more than enough. We finished the course with the chocolate carmel cheesecake. It included white and chocolate chips.  It was a massive slice and definitely amazing.  The valet staff is also exceptional.
Excellent Fresh Seafood and 5 Star Service. Cocktails were delicious, the Oceanside 2.0 in the picture. Yum!

I hosted a Friends Valentine's Day dinner tonight and the service was amazing.The staff was so friendly,  from the Valet Associate, to the hostess, to our waiter; and the food was delicious. Good food mixed with Stellar service equals money well spent. I'm very pleased with our decision to have dinner at this restaurant.
Overall the atmosphere was nice...food was okay
Terrific
Crab cakes are the best!  Tim is an excellent waiter.
From start to finish, every bite was delightful. Wine was Devine 😉 #supportindyrestaurants

We finished our "Week of Fun" at this wonderful establishment.  We began with oysters on the half shell.  My lovely wife had the Filet (no surprise) and I had the Sea Bass.  Alcohol flowed like honey.  Great evening.  The service was spot on. We will return.
Love the food. People are nice.
My food was excellent I enjoyed it was my birthday.
Perfect for a romantic date. Lobster & crab mac-cheese listed as a side, I had it as meal and couldn't get enough of it, so delicious!
Incredible crab cake, wonderful whipped mashed potatoes, and fantastic service.
Delicious food, excellent service.  Highly recommend.
Delicious, fine dining with a nice atmosphere.

Amazing dinner as always!! Fresh seafood from all over the globe. Chilian sea bass, seared sea scallops from Massachusetts, and Maine lobster were options for today. It is nice to have fresh options each time you go!
Beautiful atmosphere and great place for a date. I didn't like my food that much though.
Not as good as it usually is. Service was not as accommodating.

Very nice atmosphere. We had the calamari for an appetizer and it was just okay; very greasy and had no seasoning in the batter, definitely had better. However, the simply prepared salmon was delicious and had a nice light crisp on the outside of it. My husband had the center cut steak which was also very delicious and tender. The asparagus was really good as well.

We had a great time at Oceanaire restaurant in downtown Indianapolis.   Our waiter was very attentive. The food was excellent. The shrimp dish we ordered appeared unassuming and turned out to be authentic Italian. We ordered baked Alaskan and had a wonderful time watching the waiter do his thing with lighting it up! I told my hotel concierge to be sure and recommend Oceanaire restaurant to his guests. It was a great time and I appreciate the staff accommodating diners during 2020.
Best seafood in Indianapolis hands down. Service is amazing and so is the food
Excellent food and service
Great food and atmosphere
Wonderful service on a Christmas afternoon! My daughters and I 💘 them.
Really relaxing and quiet setting. Our waiter Tim was very friendly, helpful, and knowledgeable. The food was incredible! Highly recommended!
Food and atmosphere were awesome, little pricey but worth it. Went for 13th anniversary!!

Very nice seafood restaurant. Very attentive staff and great drinks. Ordered the chicken fried lobster and it wasn't my cup of tea. They whisked it away and quickly replaced it with crab cakes which were delicious! Green beans were yummy and seasoned well. If you love sweet cocktails, get the guava daiquiri. So good. The grapefruit mule was a hit too if you want something different from the classic. Ended the meal with the baked Alaska which is always a fun tableside presentation.
It was absolutely amazing!! Customer Service was impeccable!!
Get. The. Crab. Cakes. Soooo good!
Excellent cannot say enough good things about it. Steak bug  tender and juicy shrimp as big as  ur hand

Went to celebrate my birthday with friends and it was AMAZING!! There were 9 people in our party so because of Covid19 we had to split between 2 tables. The staff made sure we were near each other and talked to us as a group. They even printed out special menus that said "Happy Birthday from Oceanaire" at the top! The menu is much smaller than usual, but plenty of delicious offerings were still available. I ended up ordering the crab cakes and garlic green beans on the side. It was all FANTASTIC!! To my surprise bout waiter brought out an Oceanaire Baked Alaska for me  my birthday. It was visually stimulating as well as tasty!! One of my top 10 restaurants in Indy!!

This was a very special evening and one that I will treasure for a very long time. My boyfriend and I decided to come to the Oceanaire Seafood Room for our anniversary. It was the first that we had both been there and it was absolutely beautiful. It was wonderful. The menus were custom-made. The decor and overall atmosphere of the restaurant was elegant, refined, and alluded subtle class. Smooth jazz played in the background, which made our booth feel more cozy and intamite. The meal was prepared with care using only the most fresh as well as local ingredients. Lastly and certainly most important, the service was excellent. Our waiter was the most kind gentleman. He encouraged us to try new items and if we had any questions about food, then he was more than happy to inform us if we had any questions about how the food was cooked or where the ingredients were imported. Clearly, I have nothing but high praise and I will certainly looks forward to the next time that I dine at the Oceanaire.  P.S. I highly recommend the truffle mash potatoes. This had to be the most silky and smooth mash potatoes that I have ever had the good fortunate to taste. Each mouthful was literally a heavenly experience.
Tim was amazing! Food was excellent!!
Very good. Best osters we have ever had.
quality meals and service at this location is super good. Service is always super even when they have a full house. The service here is attentive. The place has a great feel to it.
The food was absolutely amazing but the main thing is the service. They are extremely attentive and very professional. Worth every penny and will be a returning customer!

This was the start of a fine dining experience.  Fresh food. Quality service from staff.  And an amazing chef. The atmosphere is very sexy.  Take your lady for lunch or have a cocktail with coworkers.
Quality Meals, yeah, my preferred treat. Service is always prompt even when they have a full house. The service was very welcoming and sociable.
Wife and I decided we needed a nice dinner out. Couldn't have picked a better place between the food and service it was excellent.
The food (except the baked Alaska) was incredible. The service was good but we were on a schedule and it took way too long to get our check and pay.
Make a reservation and mask up. Jessie, our server was awesome. Shrimp and grits as our appetizer. Main course filet mignon and shrimp with the dynamite enrichment.
Great location for Quality Meals. Went there on a Friday I think. There was fast and courteous service. The bill was reasonable I would say. Atmosphere is similar to a cafe in San Jose I loved.
A fav spot for quality quality meals. I love this place, excellent food & service. Prices were appropriate.
quality meals... super yummy. One of the best spots of its kind in the area. The service was very kind and attentive. Prices were appropriate.
quality meals at this place - great. The service was very welcoming and sociable. This place has a cool feel to it. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I liked.
Always first class and amazing service
Great food, great service Waitress was awesome *Farron*
Not a big fan of small plates for big money even though I know the how and why. Food and setting were great. Cocktails are awesome!
Great food, amazing service. Waiter was extremely helpful going thru specials and wine pairings. Will definitely be going back.
Delicious food and amazing service.
Delicious, impeccable service.

This restaurant is awesome and the food is absolutely delicious! This is my lobster that I got. My boyfriend got the truffle mashed potatoes and a ribeye steak. To drink I got a glass of Moscato and he got an espresso martini. We'll definitely be back.
A favorite spot for tasty Quality Meals. Good place to relax and unwind.  The service was very welcoming and observant. Prices are reasonable. I can see why they have a lot of great reviews.
We love to celebrate our special days here. From birthdays to anniversary

My husband and I went for our 10 year Anniversary. We had an exceptional evening. The food is always so good. What great chefs. We have never had a bad meal. Service is always great. We will always be returning customers.
My husband and I went for dinner in this place and it was great. Love to ambiance and good food too
Our favorite spot for birthdays 🥳
My husband amd I went there on our honeymoon and it was absolutely amazing. The service and food was on perfect point. It was a great atmosphere and we will definitely return.
Amazing selection of seafood, fantastic service, and elegant decor. Pricey, but definently worth splurging on.

I never would have expected the best fish I ever had was to be eaten in Indianapolis. You cannot go wrong with the artic char dynamite style. This place even smells like the ocean when you walk in. Incredible experience.

My wife and I went for our anniversary. They suggested having a reservation, when we got there it was empty. My wife’s fish dinner had literally 3 bites of food. They prepared her dinner at the table. It was overcooked. My fish was not much better. We politely expressed that we were not satisfied. They replied there isn’t anything we can do but we are sorry.  $150 bill, we walked down the street and had to get something else to eat because we were both still hungry. Tried calling a manager a few times to let them know of our experience. They didn’t care. We will never go again. We prefer Ocean Prime.
Delish and beautiful!
Scallops and cocktails were excellent!

Yes this is an expensive restaurant but it lives up to the price.  Service was great, and very upscale, the drinks were strong and presented well, and the food was great.  The fried lobster was amazing.
Amazing food , and Excellent service. My go to place when I'm in Indianapolis.

Edit—with COVID19 oceanaire found a way to continue to deliver yum. We got carry out lobster tails, crab leg & crab cake. Omg so delicious!!! I hope they continue to sell the market food to cook at home. Yum! ————————————- Best seafood in the city! The quality here is amazing which is why it’s a bit pricey.  If you know seafood you will taste the difference! The servers are very knowledgeable about everything they have & can make suggestions & answer any questions. Must tries are the crab cake, oysters, king crab & main lobster from the cold bar.
So Perfect!!!
Fabulous, great staff,food,atmosphere
My go-to for seafood downtown. Good ole standard.
Waiter was so good. Food alittle over price but good.
very delicious
Shrimp and grits were very good, and the clam chowder had a great taste. I sat at the bar, but the service was not the best.
Best seafood in the city!

We eat at OSR every time we are in Indy. It's excellent. Calamari are great! Try the chicken fried lobster. The Dover Sole is a favorite!
Opah and Wolffish. Oysters not so much, but nothing is perfect.
Excellent service

The fresh red raspberry on the creme brulee was the best part of the meal followed by the dessert and signature Manhattan. The fish entrees that my wife and I had came in last. We originally ordered the special that was subsequently to have been depleted by 8 o'clock on a slow Saturday night. The substituted fish did not come with the asparagus that was part of the special. Unfortunately, the was slightly overcooked taking it beyond the flaky stage. That made the $188 bill without tip for the one dessert, two entrees, two Manhattans, and two glasses of wine a disappointing evening for a restaurant noted for its fish.
This was our first time going. I surprised my wife for her Birthday Dinner. They went above and beyond to make the night special down to the personalized menus. Great experience

Took our collector car and business credit card and drove 2 hours from Cincinnati to have the best service and raw seafood bar with steaks it was outstanding food and service Farrin our server was professional with great detail and manners and making sure our every need from water glasses to extra dressing was taken care of my only regret is I found the restaurant under AAA and forgot to use it that could have been a 36.00 savings, Mr Ben Carroll general manager made sure we and everyone was having a great time, wish them all the very best The Smyths Indian Hill Ohio Cincinnati Sam & Lori will return, not only was it personal but it was perfect place not loud to go over the company business Thank You Oceanaire Seafood Room
Amazing tuna and atmosphere. Be aware that at night it is far dimmer inside than the pictures make it look, but that is part of the charm.
Everything was perfect! Excellent service, amazing food and atmosphere. The stoudt old fashioned was a great take on my favorite cocktail.

Amazing food, amazing service, however, this is a special occasion dining experience only.... How do you even condone $58.00 for a piece of fish, or $14.00 for 2 baked Sweet Potatoes? Also, each side is for 2 people. I may not want to have the same side as the person I am dining with. Dinner for 2 with 1 drink a piece including a tip will set you back $225.00.
Oysters were excellent.  Loved the restaurant, except our server was really surly and inattentive.  We waited 10 mins just to get the check And another 10 to get it back.  You guys weren't that busy.
Amazing food. Great service. Downton Indianapolis.

Great customer service! The food was ok...some was good,some not as much. Octopus tacos..the octopus was too chewy and slimy. Maine scallops with risotto...the scallops were great,the risotto was too salty. Got some wine and some sediment in it. Our waiter was very nice so he took the wine glass off the bill. It is a bit too expensive for the food quality. The service is amazing though. The presentation of the desert was fun but except the chocolate ice cream, was not that much about it.

Food was ok, my wife and I are regulars and were disappointed at the quality of food. Both of our dishes arrived cold. Food was overcooked and flavorless. We love the baked alaska, that too was not the amaretto we enjoy. Don't know what changed, but I will not be returning anytime soon.
Great food and atmosphere.  Crab Cakes, Ahi Tuna, Scallops all prepared wonderfully
Amazing how fresh the food is here. Only place in Indiana I'll order fare from the sea.
Best steak ever! Loved the ambiance as well!
Wonder food and service!
Amazing food and staff. My family makes it a necessary stop every time we are in the Indianapolis area. We are never disappointed and love everything we get.
The food and staff are delicious and amazing!
Amber was the best! Oysters were delightful.  Fried Black Bass was impressive.
MahiMahi was just ok.
Fresh and Great

The atmosphere is very classy, very upscale, which means pricey aswell.  White table cloth. Awesome service, Andre was great. Entrees that you can only get at the Oceanaire restaurant.   Unique seafood preparation. Interesting drink menu.   All around great experience.
Wonderful!
Food was out of this world

A little noisy, but the food and service was excellent. Had the crab cake appetizer, filet mignon with dynamite enrichment, and roasted brussel sprouts. The crab cake was to die for. The steak was cooked to perfection. Expect to pay as it pricey, but so worth it.
We love this place.  We have eaten here everytime we go to Indy. Nice staff and food
Great dining experience. Went for the devour Indy menu; had the Calamari, salmon, and key lime pie. Everything was delicious.
We had reservations and we still had to wait a half hour.

Although we had to wait 30 minutes after our reservation time to be seated, the food was very good and the service was excellent. Would recommend, as long as you are willing to spend $150+ for food and drinks.
This place was absolutely amazing. They even write happy birthday on my menu. They truly made my birthday the best ever. Farrin my waitress was super sweet and attentive. I will be back.
Excellent and delicious food, I loved the mood the spot has, and the cashiers were very nice. Will surely visit here next time.

Excellent service, phenomenal food. Nice atmosphere.  I enjoyed the 10 oz. Filet. It was done perfectly to my liking. The asparagus, and the baked sweet potato were both good.  Will come back next time in Indy.

OK - expensive menu, BUT what you get - fresh seafood (fresh! the real thing) has to cost some money to have it flown in each day. It is worth the expense. Service is friendly and very attentive. High end for a reason.
Wonderful food and ambiance. Try the chicken fried lobster!

Went here for my girlfriend’s birthday on a whim since I wanted to do a ‘fancy’ seafood place. I was not disappointed! Very nice atmosphere, calm, was quiet when we went which was nice. The food was astounding, I’ve never had tuna that melts in your mouth or cocktail shrimp that tasted so good in all my life! The Guava Daiquiri I had was very good and the little flower decor in it was a nice touch. The free baked Alaskan for her birthday was a nice touch, would definitely go again for another special occasion.

Attentive staff without being overbearing, a very good balance but what really tipped them over the top in my opinion was they were a bit on the busy side and they came over and asked if we were going to the concert (we were) after we told them we were the told us they were trying to rush the meals for the concert goers so they wouldn't be late.  That little detail made the difference to me.  They also have so many oysters to choose from and the staff is knowledgable enough to help you decide what you might or might not like.  I definitely will be going again when I'm going to Indy for a date.

My wife and I love it. It is by far our new favorite restaurant. I would highly recommend this place. If you get food plan on 200, food and alcohol plan on 300. That is with some of their most expensive food. One can eat for less.. alcohol by the bottle, cheaper than 15 dollars a glass or 59 for the bottle. They also valet.
Outstanding good eats
Yes it's very expensive.  But that's the price you pay for the best seafood you will ever eat. You will not regret going here.
Food is fine. The service is just ok
A bit noisy and pricey, but the food was excellent.  Can be a romantic dinner
Beautiful restaurant and a great seafood selection!
(Translated by Google) Seafood is delicious  (Original) Los mariscos son deliciosos
food was just alright ..not worth price

I’ve been to the Oceanaire many times and have always loved it, tonight was a big disappointment. I took a coworker and had to apologize several times for the service that we received, it was embarrassing to say the least. After the waitress told us the specials and asked us if we had any questions She acted very inconvenienced that we did indeed have questions. “Ritzy” scallops were on the menu (I usually end up always ordering the scallops,  and they are usually incredible), but  when I asked her about them, her description literally was “it’s scallops with some Ritz crackers and butter” ......(crickets, crickets, crickets).....ummmm no thank you and I’m so sorry that I have inconvenienced you by asking you to  elaborate on your menu.  Our appetizers were brought out and then our food was brought out very shortly after that with our appetizer plates still sitting on our table, no place for our food to go. So we graciously piled up all of our plates for the food runner to make room for our new Plates. Some of the appetizer plates were  taken and some where left. silverware was not replaced when taken away and We had to keep stopping different waitstaff to refill our waters or simply order a cocktail.  My guest had asked the waitress to recommend a wine pairing with her dinner and after she reminded the waitress a second time the waitress again very snuggly recommended A house zen and came and filled her glass without allowing her to taste it. I could excuse the poor service if she was really busy  and tried to apologize for her short comings but she didn’t seem to mind how our dining experience was going. the table behind us was getting good service from he.  Normally I tip between 30 and 35% and on a $230 bill that would’ve been a pretty good tip but this time I only left 18% and I still thought that was way more generous than what she deserved.  The service was so terrible it made the food mediocre, and the experience was nothing short of what a low dollar steakhouse service would give. I come in for the environment the experience and the good food  and top-notch service. Tonight service Was very disappointing.
Great food, service! 👍
The high standards I have were met. The tuna I had was succulent and the service was fantastic.
Amazing wine and service!

This is a very fine dining experience! The food is simply exquisite, and the service is marvellous! You will be given exceptional treatment, and I thoroughly recommend taking your time and savoring the entire experience. Dinner guests are under no pressure to hurry up and finish. One word of caution: this level of service and quality of food comes at a price. This is not a low budget affair. Be aware of that, and you will be able to enjoy yourselves!

Not impressed. Party of 11. Maybe for starters, all but the steaks were cold. The scallop and steaks were flavorful. The salmon would probably be great but for the temperature. Last, don’t for one second believe we received the ordered weight in King crab legs. Thankfully, the dining companions were phenomenal.
Loved the lobster roll special! Great menu, staff and location
Great food and service. Never disappoints.

Heard there's something of a transition going on here, which might explain my experience...but the lobster bisque was AWFUL and the decór was badly dated. Shrimp app was only ok, and the tuna was tough.
Great food, servers were attentive, funny, and very knowledgeable. Would recommend if you are in the area. P.S. the lobster Mac and cheese was spectacular
It was excellent. Excellent food.

The Truffled fries and Rockefeller oysters are divine. The lobster grilled cheese is absolutely savory. You will not be disappointed by the food here. My only complaint is that our waitress was very intrusive. She invited herself into many conversations and referred to several items on the menu as underwhelming, one of which we ordered anyway and LOVED.
Amazing! Terrific crab and oysters!

Absolutely delicious with an attentive staff. The cedar roasted salmon was absolutely perfect, and they make the best mojitos I've ever had. Michael our waiter is top of the line, always attentive and ready to explain anything and everything on the menu to us. Beautiful and enjoyable atmosphere.
Very nice restaurant, great service, but a bit disappointed with the fish and chips. Fish didn't have much flavor. Get the truffle fries.
Excellent food, great service.
Amazing shrimp scampi
I would usually not go away from fish, simply prepared, however, fried lobster was nice but the winner...Grilled Oyster Rock!  Yummmmm!!
The angry sauce will make anything on the menu even better. Scallops were cooked perfectly and possibly the best old fashioned in town.
Always warm an welcome drinks are really good the food is always great
Always great food & service, but $$ seems to gone even higher. Almost getting to be not worth it.
Food was excellent. Atmosphere was a little stuffy for me but a good place for great seafood!
Always a winner!  Great selection of prime seafood, served in an upscale downtown setting.  Friendly, knowledgeable staff, amazing food, full bar.  We've never been disappointed.
Great food and service. Atmosphere is very cozy and calm. Crab cakes are always a must! Staff are attentive and kind.
So delicious!

Oceanaire is definitely a special treat place, but we enjoy going there. We went to a world renown seafood place in Hawaii, and Oceanaire is just as good.  We love sitting in the cozy booths.  The service is always friendly.
Always amazing crab legs
Fantastic food. Fantastic service. Huge portions on the sides & deserts.

I love it! Great place to celebrate a special occasion! Great food!

Good food, pricey for what you get though, a bit outdated inside.
Wow great atmosphere. Our waiter nick was the best. Had to eat in a rush and they made it happen. Thanks oceanaire staff. We will definitely be back.
Great food, good prices
Great food and excellent service bu at a near premium price
Good seafood when downtown

I was very pleased with the menu. I started with the poke, and it was great. I would of liked it better if it was not already on a chip. I ordered the Sesame seared tuna for dinner. It was cooked perfectly, still cool in the center. I would like to see more choices for sides. I went with asparagus. Would of liked a rice or steamed vegetables. Overall I would recommend eating here.
The food was very good but i did not care for where we where sitted under salmon:( I love atmosphere and there was none. It was a special occasion for us.
One of the best meals we've had! Jose was fantastic!
Food and dining experience is superb! Worth it! ❤
Great food great service
Great atmosphere, but took over 2 hours to receive our 3 courses. The manager did comp a round of beverages for our table due to the wait. Food was delicious!
Great service. Amazing ambiance. Superb food.
My favorite restaurant to take business associates and loved ones
Great place in Indy. Love the Jazz Music.
Always great food. Allow time for an upscale, unhurried service. Great devour menu.
Place was excellent
Awesome service and great food. Try the crab whipped potatoes!
Fantastic dinner, I can't wait to return
Probably shouldn't have ordered a steak at a seafood restaurant
Excellent food.  Classy atmosphere.  Great service.  A bit pricey but worth it.
Nice place but our waitress was bad..Food was exceptional,  but you can never get past the server who was always MIA.
This place is amazing!  Perfect atmosphere,  perfect seating, perfect food, perfect dessert.! Totally recommend this place for dinner with any sea food lovers out there!

We sat at the bar and ordered the fish tacos with a couple of beers. The beer was cold and the food was good, however the bartender had a large group and we never saw her again. Since we were unable to order another drink, we decided to go elsewhere. I had to stop a waiter from the dining area to ask for our tab.
Very nice, very fresh. Good service.
The rockfish was amazing
Food and service is world class
Extremely overpriced for the quality and quantity. I've been twice, both times it wasn't good.
Amber and the bar staff are amazing.  The food is exquisite

We are fairly frequent diners here and  appreciate the well prepared seafood. This time we visited on a recent Monday, and both my husband and I agree this was the best meal yet.  We were immediately greeted, reservations confirmed and seated our preference. Staff quickly  provided water and menus. Heather our waitstaff was fabulous!  She was personable, knowledgeable about the restaurant, and enthusiastic yet very professional (if you think about it,  those are four  qualities that are very hard to meld into one person, but she rocked it!). We apreciated   Heather's knowledge with the menu, and  she expressed the highest confidence in what she felt were several of the best choices (we asked). We usually order all types of shellfish (always delicious!), but this time we stepped out of our comfort xone and settled on a couple of her recommendations and a couple of our favorites. We started with a cup of clam chowder and the baby octopus with Brussels sprouts for appetizers. The chowder was, - as usual  -  rich and buttery with plenty of clams. Heaven! We were completely blown away with how good the  baby octopus tasted  -  perfectly seared meat, and the Brussels sprouts were simply the best we had.- the flavors were executed the best way  - no hint of any  bitterness or sulfur often found with this vegetable.  For dinner we had the seared fresh Washington Troll King Salmon with lump blue crab, caper and beurre blanc,  and the Alaska Halibut cheeks with carmelized onion and blue cheese butter.  The salmon was perfectly prepared,  and had a very generous top of tender crabmeat along with the gentle seasoning and very light sauce .  My hubby can generally take or leave salmon, but this time he cleaned his plate with gusto!  The halibut cheeks were a symphony of complimentary flavors. The cheeks were 'almost' a touch too spicy by themselves.  But when each bite included the spicy cheek with a bit  of  carmelized onion and a touch of  blue butter  ..... wow, the taste was truly amazing! We asked about the chef of the night,  and Heather credited Executive chef Aaron and student chef Kellem. So,  Heather,  Aaron and Kellem,  along with the other very attentive and professional staff this evening,  thank you for the best anniversary dinner we've had!
